
# nix-dev-env

Cross-platform user package environment powered by **Nix flakes**.

This repository defines a reproducible set of user tools that can be installed on macOS and Linux using Nix. The goal is to maintain a single source of truth for development packages across machines.

Packages are bundled into a single installable profile.

---

## Requirements

Install Nix with flakes enabled:

```bash
sh <(curl -L https://nixos.org/nix/install) --daemon
```

Enable flakes (if not already enabled) add this like to the nix.conf

```bash
experimental-features = nix-command flakes
```

---

## Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/dev-env.git
cd dev-env
```

Install the environment:

```bash
nix profile install .#default --profile dev-env
```

This installs all defined packages into a reusable Nix profile.

---

## Updating Packages

After pulling changes:

```bash
git pull
nix profile upgrade dev-env
```

---

## Reinstall / Apply Changes

If packages were modified in `flake.nix`:

```bash
nix profile install .#default --profile dev-env --force
```

---

## List Installed Profiles

```bash
nix profile list
```

Show detailed information:

```bash
nix profile list --json
```

---

## Remove Environment

```bash
nix profile remove dev-env
```

---

## Adding Packages

Edit `flake.nix`:

```nix
commonPackages = with pkgs; [
  neovim
  tmux
  git
];
```

Then apply:

```bash
nix profile install .#default --profile dev-env --force
```

